   "source": [
    "# Virtual Screening with a pharmacophore"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "e5740f66-ff59-4eca-b38e-de1984a0a5bc",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "remove-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "4fc5b8ef89a6428eb9848d85a22afdfc",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": []
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pyunitwizard as puw\n",
    "import openpharmacophore as oph\n",
    "from openpharmacophore import mol_db"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2373963a-5106-4191-9a4c-cc51b376e4ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We want to screen a database of molecules with a pharmacophore to find potential matches. \n",
    "We start by defining our pharmacophore model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "110b331e-0761-4c84-a2c7-b1101697b10a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pharmacophore = oph.Pharmacophore([\n",
    "    oph.PharmacophoricPoint(\n",
    "        feat_type=\"hb acceptor\",\n",
    "        center=puw.quantity([2.35, 1.94, -0.68], \"angstroms\"),\n",
    "        radius=puw.quantity(1.0, \"angstroms\"),\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    oph.PharmacophoricPoint(\n",
    "        feat_type=\"hydrophobicity\",\n",
    "        center=puw.quantity([1.57, -2.53, 2.15], \"angstroms\"),\n",
    "        radius=puw.quantity(1.0, \"angstroms\"),\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    oph.PharmacophoricPoint(\n",
    "        feat_type=\"aromatic ring\",\n",
    "        center=puw.quantity([6.19, 1.34, -1.36], \"angstroms\"),\n",
    "        radius=puw.quantity(1.0, \"angstroms\"),\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "ae9f7c32-dfdd-4909-8f16-4e004d04c67d",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "remove-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "d7f2b094a7324a4a91c5b1f82e7ba788",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "NGLWidget()"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "viewer = oph.Viewer()\n",
    "viewer.add_components([pharmacophore])\n",
    "viewer.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee07edf1-6c57-473b-805d-bbc7b41471b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will create a database of molecules loading them from different files"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "94ad283d-27a9-4b06-a78a-ff9a9c4c670a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "file1 = \"../data/screening/ligands_1.smi\"\n",
    "file2 = \"../data/screening/ligands_2.smi\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "5550c015-adf4-4bc2-a2f6-d7c453e0a055",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Smiles Name\n",
      "[H]/N=C(\\C1CCC(CC1)CNC(=O)[C@@H]2C=C(CN3N2C(=O)N(C3=O)CC(c4ccccc4)c5ccccc5)C)/N IH2\n",
      "CN[C@H](Cc1ccccc1)C(=O)N2CCC[C@H]2C(=O)NCC3CCC(CC3)N MIN\n",
      "c1ccc(cc1)S(=O)(=O)CCN2C(=O)N3CC=C[C@H](N3C2=O)C(=O)NC4CCC(CC4)c5cnc([nH]5)N 00R\n",
      "c1ccc(cc1)S(=O)(=O)CCN2C(=O)N3CC=C[C@H](N3C2=O)C(=O)NCC4CCC(CC4)N 00P\n",
      "[H]/N=C(/c1ccc(cc1)C[C@H](C(=O)N2CCCCC2)NC(=O)CNS(=O)(=O)c3ccc4ccccc4c3)\\N MID"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "! cat {file1}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "6688be4d-ea7a-4e3f-b2a3-c0b7abf4b780",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Smiles Name\n",
      "[H]/N=C(\\c1ccc2c(c1)cc([nH]2)C(=O)N3CCC(CC3)Cc4ccccc4)/N BPP\n",
      "CCC1CCN(CC1)C(=O)[C@H](CCCNC(=[NH2+])N)NS(=O)(=O)c2cccc3c2cccc3N(C)C 0ZI\n",
      "C[C@H]1CN2c3c(cc(cc3NC2=S)Cl)CN1CC=C(C)C TB9\n",
      "CC(C)c1c(n(c(n1)COC(=O)N)Cc2ccncc2)Sc3cc(cc(c3)Cl)Cl S11\n",
      "CC(C)OC(=O)N1c2cc(ccc2NC(=S)[C@@H]1CSC)OC HBY"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "! cat {file2}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "bbc92f60-39fa-4aa0-bb67-5fdf20b162a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "db = mol_db.MolDB()\n",
    "db.from_file_list([file1, file2], header=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "48d34823-0e8c-4aa7-b2c4-53b53d133c83",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now create a virtual screening object to which will pass our pharmacophore\n",
    "and our molecule db"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "acbc22f0-cd66-4d5c-b911-ad17ab410547",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "4 molecule matched the pharmacophore\n",
      "6 molecule failed to match the pharmacophore\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "screener = oph.VirtualScreening([pharmacophore])\n",
    "screener.screen(db)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"{len(screener.matches[0])} molecule matched the pharmacophore\")\n",
    "print(f\"{screener.fails[0]} molecule failed to match the pharmacophore\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fbb5db9b-fcbc-44a6-b43e-7329925492a5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We inspect the molecules that matched the pharmachore along with their alignment scores (RMSD)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "dcbcd403-b5d1-4c43-97ce-c35bd80ab1cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "RMSDs [0.8177257515854292, 0.8517769586370709, 0.7687604258063847, 0.9831765173894478]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ligands = [m.ligand for m in screener.matches[0]]\n",
    "legends = [\n",
    "    m.ligand.to_rdkit().GetProp(\"_Name\") for m in screener.matches[0]\n",
    "]\n",
    "scores = [m.rmsd for m in screener.matches[0]]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"RMSDs\", scores)\n",
    "oph.draw_ligands(\n",
    "    ligands=ligands, \n",
    "    n_per_row=4,\n",
    "    legends=legends\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "07c369ff-ccf3-47c9-8602-a85ff35bdc23",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We visualize the aligned ligands and the pharmacophore"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "10a92e6d-4d74-4b76-a6f9-0231d3cceb33",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "remove-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "ff1b96ac97474a449affdee461d5455e",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "NGLWidget()"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "idx = 0\n",
    "viewer = oph.Viewer()\n",
    "viewer.add_components([ligands[idx], pharmacophore])\n",
    "viewer.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6b6ae121-e412-43a7-b2e3-4274d23cddf9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<img src=\"../../../_static/screening.png\">"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "11bc1551-2d52-4843-bc66-68a4cde73f20",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "remove-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Save pharmacophore image so it can be viewed in the documentation\n",
    " \n",
    "import time\n",
    "import threading\n",
    "\n",
    "save = False\n",
    "\n",
    "def save_image(view):\n",
    "    im = view.render_image()\n",
    "    while not im.value:\n",
    "        time.sleep(0.1)\n",
    "    save_path = \"../../../_static/screening.png\"\n",
    "    with open(save_path, \"wb\") as fp:\n",
    "        fp.write(im.value)    \n",
    "\n",
    "def generate_image():\n",
    "    thread = threading.Thread(target=save_image, args=(viewer.to_nglview(),), daemon=True)\n",
    "    thread.start()\n",
    "    \n",
    "\n",
    "if save:\n",
    "    generate_image()"
   ]
  }
 ],
